revision.text:
The '''1977–78 Cuban National Series''' was a watershed in that it coincided with [[Cuba]]'s administrative restructuring of 1977, which created [[Provinces of Cuba|fourteen provinces]]. Pinar del Río's Vegueros won the title, with a slim victory over [[Havana]]'s [[Industriales]].
==Restructuring== Teams were renamed along these lines, many taking the names of their new locations.
Three provinces kept two teams: *[[Havana]] (city): [[Industriales]] and [[Metropolitanos]] *[[Pinar del Río Province]]: Vegueros and Forestales *[[Matanzas Province]]: Citricultores and Henequeneros
Additionally, the special administrative area of [[Isla de la Juventud]] had its own team, despite not being a province.
This league structure survives today in a similar form.
