'''El-Entag El-Harby Sporting Club''' ({{lang-ar|'''نادي الانتاج الحربي الرياضي'''}} ; {{lang-en|''' Military Production'''}}) is a [[Cairo]]-based [[Association football|football]] club in the [[Egyptian Premier League]], representing the Ministry of War Production. Its promotion to the Premier League for the [[Egyptian Premier League 2009–10|2009–10 season]] marked its first appearance at that level.

==History==
In 2004 The Club Played For Youth At This Year They Managed Under Mohamed Abdel-all Who Managed Unknown Club In UAE Afer Entag Harby And The Top Players At This Moment Is Abdelrahman Mohamed And Amr Mohamed.{{clarify|reason=The previous sentence makes no sense in English.|date=November 2015}}
After a long and an intense race with [[Al Nasr Egypt|Al Nasr]] and El Dakhleya in [[2008-09 Egyptian Second Division|2008–09]], El-Entag El-Harby secured its first appearance ever in the [[Egyptian Premier League]]. The team needed their last match that season (2–2 tie with GASCO) to win promotion. In preparation for its premier league campaign, El-Entag El-Harby appointed [[Tarek Yehia]] as the new manager. Yehia quickly looked for the option of signing experienced Egyptian players that could lead the team to prevent relegation. He signed players such as [[Mohamed Aboul Ela]] ([[Zamalek SC|Zamalek]] former captain), [[Mostafa Kamal (footballer born 1973)|Mostafa Kamal]] (Veteran Goal Keeper), Hassan Mousa, and others.

Tarek Yehia enjoyed great success with his team. Surprisingly, El-Entag El-Harby finished 7th in its first season at the Premier League level ([[2009–10 Egyptian Premier League|2009–10]]).<ref>[http://www.rsssf.com/tablese/egy2010.html "Egypt 2009/10"]. RSSF. Retrieved on 9 June 2010.</ref> However, Yehia's era at the club lasted for only that season. He preferred to move to newly promoted [[Misr Lel Makasa]]. [[Osama Orabi]] replaced him.<ref>Tarek, Sherif [http://filgoal.com/English/News.aspx?NewsID=68818 "Production install Orabi as new boss"]. Filgoal, 2010-06-06. Retrieved on 6 June 2010.</ref>

