'''Outpoint''' is a term frequently used in [[boxing]] to describe a situation in which one boxer is awarded more points than his or her opponent by the judges, but does not [[knock out]] that opponent.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://boxing.about.com/b/a/205307.htm |title=Klitschko Climbs Off Deck to Outpoint Peter |publisher=Boxing.about.com |date=2005-09-25 |accessdate=2011-11-11}}</ref>

