{{Infobox stadium | stadium_name = Sport Toplumy Stadium | logo_image = | image = | fullname = | location = [[Mary, Turkmenistan]] | coordinates = {{Coord|37.607191|61.845672|type:landmark_scale:3000|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | broke_ground = | built = | opened = 2009 | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = [[Mary, Turkmenistan|Mary]] city Administration | tenants = [[FC Merw]] | surface = [[Grass]] | record_attendance = | construction_cost = | architect = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor = Kılıç İnşaat | project_manager = | main_contractors = | former_names = | seating_capacity = 10,000 | dimensions = }} '''Sport Toplumy Stadium''' is a [[multi-purpose stadium]] in [[Mary, Turkmenistan]]. It is currently used mostly for [[football (soccer)|football]] matches and serves as the home stadium for [[FC Merw]]. The stadium holds 10,000 people.<ref>[http://turkmenistan.gov.tm/?id=5645]</ref><ref>[http://www.turkmenistan.gov.tm/?id=3719]</ref>
== History == The sports complex opened in May 2009. First match was between [[FC Merw]] and afghan FC Esteghlal Herat (6:0).<ref>[http://news.uzreport.uz/news_10_r_63707.html]</ref> Construction works carried out by Turkish company Kılıç İnşaat . The project cost $20 million.<ref>[http://www.trend.az/casia/turkmenistan/1451362.html]</ref>
