'''Ugyen Academy Football Club''' is a football club from [[Punakha]], [[Bhutan]], based at [[Lekeythang Football Field|Lekeythang]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/teams/bhutan/ugyen-academy-fc/23660/|title=Ugyen Academy FC|website=soccerway.com|publisher=Perform Group|accessdate=23 July 2014}}</ref> They won the Bhutan National League title in [[2013 Bhutan National League|2013]] and represented Bhutan at the [[2014 AFC President's Cup]].

== History ==
Ugyen Academy's first appearance in the national league was in the [[2012–13 Bhutan National League|2012–13 season]], where they finished third behind eventual champions [[Yeedzin F.C.|Yeedzin]] and [[Druk Pol F.C.|Druk Pol]],<ref name="RSSSF2012">{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesb/bhutan2012.html|title=Bhutan 2012|last=Schöggl|first=Hans|last2=Stokkermans|first2=Karel|last3=Jigmi|first3=Sonam|date=28 Feb 2013|website=www.rsssf.com|publisher=[[Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation]]|accessdate=23 July 2014}}</ref> and were involved in the season's highest scoring game, an 8–1 victory over [[Samtse FC|Samtse]].<ref name="RSSSF2012" /> The [[2013 Bhutan National League|following season]] they won the Bhutan National league, by a point from Yeedzin, losing only once, 2–4 to [[Thimphu City F.C.|Thimphu]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesb/bhutan2013.html|title=Bhutan 2013|last=Schöggl|first=Hans|last2=Stokkermans|first2=Karel|last3=Jigmi|first3=Sonam|date=20 Feb 2014|website=www.rsssf.com|publisher=[[Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation]]|accessdate=23 July 2014}}</ref> By winning the national league, Ugyen Academy were awarded Bhutan's berth in the [[2014 AFC President's Cup]], their first appearance in any form of continental competition. They were drawn in Group A for the group stage, along with [[Sheikh Russel KC|Sheikh Russel]] of Bangladesh, [[KRL F.C.|KRL]] of Pakistan and [[Air Force SC|Sri Lanka Air Force]].<ref name="AFC2">{{cite web|url=http://www.the-afc.com/en/tournaments/clubs/afc-presidents-cup/27986-afc-president-cup-draw.html|title=AFC President’s Cup 2014: Group Stage Draw|publisher=AFC|date=28 March 2014|accessdate=28 March 2014}}</ref> All the matches were played in Sri Lanka,<ref name="AFC2" /> and Ugyen Academy lost all three matches without scoring and conceding 8 goals.

