Ugyen Academy again took part in the [[2014 Bhutan National League#National League|National League]] the following season. They suffered a mediocre start to the season, drawing with eventual winners [[Druk United F.C.|Druk United]] and losing to then leaders [[Thimphu City F.C.|Thimphu City]] to find themselves lying in fourth place at the halfway stage.<ref name="RSSSF2014">{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesb/bhutan2014.html|title=Bhutan 2014|last=Stokkermans|first=Karel|last2=Jigmi|first2=Sonam|date=22 May 2014|website=www.rsssf.com|publisher=[[Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation]]|accessdate=27 June 2014}}</ref> The team rallied in the second half however, winning all their matches bar a loss to [[Druk Star F.C.|Druk Star]] to end the season in second place, narrowly losing out on both the title and qualification for the [[2015 AFC Cup]] on goal difference to Druk United.<ref name="RSSSF2014" />

